      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've been watching the starlings in the park for the last three weeks and it's not just random anymore. they are definitely communicating something about the pressure changes. i can actually tell what they're saying by the way the murmurations shift right before a storm hits. it's like i can decode the sequence. has anyone else ever documented this kind of direct link between avian patterns and micro-climates?",
